## 4. Firmware Data Flow

### 4.1 Sampling & Signal Processing Loop (100 ms / 10 Hz)

{% mermaid
   code="\nflowchart TD\n    START([FreeRTOS main loop\\n100ms tick]) --> READ\n\n    READ[adc_oneshot_read × 5 channels\\n12-bit values 0–4095]\n    READ --> EMA\n\n    EMA[\"EMA Filter per channel\\nema = α × raw + (1−α) × prev\\nα = 0.2\"]\n    EMA --> MODEQ{Current Mode?}\n\n    MODEQ -->|CALIBRATE| CALUPD[\"update_calibration()\\nExpand cal_min / cal_max\\nto observed extremes\"]\n    MODEQ -->|TRAIN or INFER| CALUSE[Use stored cal_min / cal_max\\nor fall back to dynamic window]\n    CALUPD --> NORM\n    CALUSE --> NORM\n\n    NORM[\"preprocess_sample()\\nnorm = (ema − min) / (max − min)\\nclamp to 0.0 – 1.0\"]\n    NORM --> WRBUF\n\n    WRBUF[\"Write to circular buffer\\nglobal_norm_buffer[ch][global_idx]\\nglobal_idx = (global_idx+1) % 32\"]\n    WRBUF --> ACTCHK\n\n    ACTCHK[\"setMinMax() — Activity Check\\nif max−min < 100 for all channels\\n→ isDisabled = true\"]\n    ACTCHK --> MODEQ2{Mode + Disabled?}\n\n    MODEQ2 -->|INFER + active\\n+ 1s elapsed| LINEARISE\n    MODEQ2 -->|TRAIN + store flag set| SAVETASK\n    MODEQ2 -->|otherwise| TELEMETRY\n\n    LINEARISE[\"Unroll circular buffer\\ninto contiguous 160-float array\\n(chronological order)\"]\n    LINEARISE --> KNN[run_knn_inference]\n\n    SAVETASK[\"save_buffer_to_spiffs(label)\\nAppend sample_record_t to\\n/spiffs/dataset.bin\"]\n    SAVETASK --> TELEMETRY\n\n    KNN --> TELEMETRY\n\n    TELEMETRY[\"Print telemetry over Serial\\n>r[i]:[raw]\\n>[i]:[mapped 0–100]\\n>mode:[MODE]\\n>d:[disabled]\\nBest Match: [Label] (Dist: X.XX)\"]\n    TELEMETRY --> START\n" /%}

### 4.2 k-NN Inference Engine

{% mermaid
   code="\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant ML as main_loop\n    participant KNN as run_knn_inference\n    participant FS as SPIFFS / dataset.bin\n    participant DSP as ESP-DSP SIMD\n\n    ML->>KNN: linearised_norm_buf[160], k=3\n    KNN->>FS: fopen(dataset.bin, \"rb\")\n    KNN->>KNN: init top_k[k] with distance=∞\n\n    loop Read INFERENCE_BATCH_SIZE=20 records at a time\n        FS-->>KNN: batch of sample_record_t {label, data[160]}\n        loop For each record in batch\n            KNN->>DSP: dsps_sub_f32(live, stored, diff, 160)\n            DSP-->>KNN: diff[160]\n            KNN->>DSP: dsps_dotprod_f32(diff, diff, &sum_sq, 160)\n            DSP-->>KNN: sum of squares\n            KNN->>KNN: dist = sqrt(sum_sq)\n            KNN->>KNN: update_top_k() — insert-sort into top_k if closer\n        end\n    end\n\n    KNN->>FS: fclose\n    KNN-->>ML: print \"Best Match: [label] (Dist: X.XX)\"\n    Note over KNN: Timing logged via esp_timer_get_time()\n" /%}

### 4.3 Dataset Storage Format (SPIFFS)

Each call to `store <label>` appends one binary record to `/spiffs/dataset.bin`:

```
sample_record_t {
    char  label[16];        // null-terminated gesture name
    float data[160];        // 5 channels × 32 samples, chronological
}

```

Records are read back sequentially during inference; no indexing structure is needed given the small dataset size typical of k-NN gesture libraries.

---

## 5. Communication Protocol

The ESP32 emits a structured telemetry stream over USB-Serial (115200 baud) that the dashboard parses:

{% table %}
- Frame
- Direction
- Meaning
---
- `>r[i]:[val]`
- ESP → Browser
- Raw 12-bit ADC value for channel `i`
---
- `>[i]:[val]`
- ESP → Browser
- Mapped 0–100 value for progress bars
---
- `>max[i]:[val]` / `>min[i]:[val]`
- ESP → Browser
- Current calibration bounds per channel
---
- `>mode:[MODE]`
- ESP → Browser
- Active mode string (TRAIN / INFER / CALIBRATE)
---
- `>d:[0/1]`
- ESP → Browser
- Activity disabled flag
---
- `>time:[us]`
- ESP → Browser
- Inference duration in microseconds
---
- `Best Match: [Label] (Dist: X.XX)`
- ESP → Browser
- Top k-NN prediction result
---
- `>list:[id]:[label]`
- ESP → Browser
- Dataset record enumeration
---
- `mode train` / `mode infer` / `mode calibrate`
- Browser → ESP
- Switch operating mode
---
- `store <label>`
- Browser → ESP
- Capture current buffer as labelled training sample
---
- `k <n>`
- Browser → ESP
- Set number of k-NN neighbours (1–10)
---
- `list` / `clear` / `read <id>`
- Browser → ESP
- Dataset management commands
{% /table %}

BLE UART (Nordic NUS profile via NimBLE) exposes the same command interface wirelessly, enabling Android/BLE control without USB.

